<li>Michael, Jack. (1975) "<a href="http://www.behavior.org/journals_BP/2000/JackMichael.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.behavior.org/journals_BP/2000/JackMichael.pdf" rel="nofollow">Positive and negative reinforcement, a distinction that is no longer necessary; or a better way to talk about bad things</a>." <i>Behaviorism</i>, 3 (1): 33-44.</li>
